00:12:26.690 --> 00:12:28.690
On the tongue of Umar radiallahu ta'ala

00:12:28.690 --> 00:12:30.690
So the Prophet

00:12:30.690 --> 00:12:32.690
Referred to him as a muhadath

00:12:32.690 --> 00:12:34.690
The muhadath I already mentioned is

00:12:34.690 --> 00:12:36.690
Al mulhamoon

00:12:36.690 --> 00:12:38.690
The ones when they speak

00:12:38.690 --> 00:12:40.690
Things go in line with them

00:12:40.690 --> 00:12:42.690
And the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:12:42.690 --> 00:12:44.690
Also said that Allah placed

00:12:44.690 --> 00:12:46.690
The truth on the tongue of Umar

00:12:46.690 --> 00:12:48.690
And his heart

00:12:48.690 --> 00:12:50.690
And the sahabas recognized that

00:12:50.690 --> 00:12:52.690
Including Ali ibn Abi Talib

00:12:52.690 --> 00:12:54.690
Ali radiallahu ta'ala

00:12:54.690 --> 00:12:56.690
He used to say

00:13:02.690 --> 00:13:04.690
That we never found it to be far

00:13:04.690 --> 00:13:06.690
That tranquility would be coming

00:13:06.690 --> 00:13:08.690
From the mouth of Umar radiallahu ta'ala

00:13:08.690 --> 00:13:10.690
And even he himself

00:13:10.690 --> 00:13:12.690
Umar mentioned three times that

00:13:12.690 --> 00:13:14.690
He said things which the Quran

00:13:14.690 --> 00:13:16.690
Came in support of him

00:13:16.690 --> 00:13:18.690
Umar radiallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:13:20.690 --> 00:13:22.690
I went in line with my Lord in three things

00:13:22.690 --> 00:13:24.690
Umar said it and then the Quran

00:13:24.690 --> 00:13:26.690
Came to support him

00:13:26.690 --> 00:13:28.690
The issue related to

00:13:28.690 --> 00:13:30.690
Maqami Ibrahim

00:13:30.690 --> 00:13:32.690
And the issue of the hijab

00:13:32.690 --> 00:13:34.690
When he came to the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:13:34.690 --> 00:13:36.690
The hijab

00:13:36.690 --> 00:13:38.690
And then the ayah came down

00:13:42.690 --> 00:13:44.690
And also the ayah

00:13:46.690 --> 00:13:48.690
Those three verses they came in support

00:13:48.690 --> 00:13:50.690
With Umar radiallahu ta'ala

00:13:50.690 --> 00:13:52.690
Rather the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:13:52.690 --> 00:13:54.690
Had a dream regarding

00:13:54.690 --> 00:13:56.690
Umar ibn Umar and he said

00:13:56.690 --> 00:13:58.690
I heard the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam say

00:13:58.690 --> 00:14:00.690
I was sleeping

00:14:00.690 --> 00:14:06.690
A cup of milk was brought to me

00:14:06.690 --> 00:14:08.690
And I drank from the cup

00:14:08.690 --> 00:14:10.690
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:14:10.690 --> 00:14:12.690
The Prophet said I had a dream

00:14:12.690 --> 00:14:14.690
And in this dream

00:14:14.690 --> 00:14:16.690
A cup of milk was brought to me

00:14:16.690 --> 00:14:18.690
And I drank

00:14:18.690 --> 00:14:20.690
I drank from it

00:14:24.690 --> 00:14:26.690
And I saw that the

00:14:26.690 --> 00:14:28.690
The quench

00:14:28.690 --> 00:14:30.690
Of the milk

00:14:30.690 --> 00:14:32.690
The Prophet said he drank it

00:14:32.690 --> 00:14:34.690
He drank so much that the milk

00:14:34.690 --> 00:14:36.690
Was coming out of his nails

00:14:38.690 --> 00:14:40.690
Then I gave

00:14:40.690 --> 00:14:42.690
Whatever was left over

00:14:42.690 --> 00:14:44.690
From my milk

00:14:44.690 --> 00:14:46.690
The Prophet said I got

00:14:46.690 --> 00:14:48.690
Then I gave it to Umar

00:14:48.690 --> 00:14:52.060
I said Umar finish it off I can't

00:14:52.060 --> 00:14:54.060
And then Umar started to drink it

00:14:54.060 --> 00:14:56.060
The people they said

00:14:56.060 --> 00:14:58.060
What's your interpretation of that dream

00:14:58.060 --> 00:15:00.060
What does that mean that you drank the milk and gave it to Umar

00:15:00.060 --> 00:15:02.060
What does that mean

00:15:02.060 --> 00:15:04.060
The Prophet said knowledge

00:15:04.060 --> 00:15:06.060
Umar is going to take knowledge like that

00:15:06.060 --> 00:15:08.060
Allahu Akbar

00:15:08.060 --> 00:15:10.060
The vastness of

00:15:10.060 --> 00:15:12.060
The knowledge of Umar

00:15:12.060 --> 00:15:14.060
Abu Saeed also mentioned that

00:15:14.060 --> 00:15:16.060
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam said

00:15:16.060 --> 00:15:18.060
The Prophet had another dream

00:15:18.060 --> 00:15:20.060
I was sleeping the Prophet said

00:15:24.060 --> 00:15:26.060
The Prophet said I had a dream

00:15:26.060 --> 00:15:28.060
The people were

00:15:28.060 --> 00:15:30.060
Being brought to me and they were wearing

00:15:30.060 --> 00:15:32.060
A garment

00:15:34.060 --> 00:15:36.060
People's garments were

00:15:36.060 --> 00:15:38.060
The length of the garment were different

00:15:38.060 --> 00:15:40.060
Some people were reaching their shin

00:15:40.060 --> 00:15:42.060
Some people were reaching this some were reaching that

00:15:42.060 --> 00:15:44.060
Different places of their bodies

00:15:48.060 --> 00:15:50.060
Umar came by me

00:15:52.060 --> 00:15:54.060
Umar was wearing a kameesh

00:15:54.060 --> 00:15:56.060
His kameesh was dragging on the ground

00:15:56.060 --> 00:15:58.060
It was very long

00:16:00.060 --> 00:16:02.060
What's your interpretation

00:16:02.060 --> 00:16:04.060
Of the dream or message of Allah

00:16:04.060 --> 00:16:06.060
The Prophet said

00:16:06.060 --> 00:16:08.060
This shows

00:16:08.060 --> 00:16:10.060
The vastness of Umar's religion

00:16:10.060 --> 00:16:12.060
How vast it is

00:16:12.060 --> 00:16:14.060
My brothers and sisters inside benefit

00:16:14.060 --> 00:16:16.060
He speaks about it in great details

00:16:16.060 --> 00:16:18.060
He does touch on it

00:16:18.060 --> 00:16:20.060
In his kitab

00:16:20.060 --> 00:16:22.060
He also speaks about it in his kitab

00:16:22.060 --> 00:16:24.060
And in other places of his works

00:16:24.060 --> 00:16:26.060
Ibn Taymiyya has already previously spoken about it

00:16:26.060 --> 00:16:28.060
Other great scholars have touched on this

00:16:28.060 --> 00:16:30.060
And that is this issue of a dream

00:16:30.060 --> 00:16:32.060
Doesn't necessarily mean

00:16:32.060 --> 00:16:34.060
That it's a shara'a ruling

00:16:36.060 --> 00:16:38.060
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam here mentioned

00:16:38.060 --> 00:16:40.060
Umar's garment would be dragging on the ground

00:16:40.060 --> 00:16:42.060
That doesn't mean

00:16:42.060 --> 00:16:44.060
That it's permissible for a man's garment to drag

00:16:44.060 --> 00:16:46.060
As we know

00:16:46.060 --> 00:16:48.060
The man's garment is not allowed to be

00:16:48.060 --> 00:16:50.060
Below his ankles

00:16:50.060 --> 00:16:52.060
So what you see in your dream

00:16:52.060 --> 00:16:54.060
Doesn't necessarily mean it's a reality

00:16:54.060 --> 00:16:56.060
What do I mean by that brothers and sisters

00:16:56.060 --> 00:16:58.060
Someone might see

00:16:58.060 --> 00:17:00.060
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam in their dream

00:17:00.060 --> 00:17:02.060
As they think they have

00:17:02.060 --> 00:17:04.060
They assume they saw the Prophet in their dream

00:17:04.060 --> 00:17:06.060
Sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:17:06.060 --> 00:17:08.060
And what they see in their dream says to them

00:17:08.060 --> 00:17:10.060
You don't need to pray dhur or asr

00:17:10.060 --> 00:17:12.060
Or maghrib or isha or fajr

00:17:12.060 --> 00:17:14.060
And the person wakes up

00:17:14.060 --> 00:17:16.060
Wakes up and said

00:17:16.060 --> 00:17:18.060
I saw the Prophet in my dream

00:17:18.060 --> 00:17:20.060
And since I saw the Prophet in my dream

00:17:20.060 --> 00:17:22.060
And he told me I don't need to pray

00:17:22.060 --> 00:17:24.060
I no longer have to pray

00:17:24.060 --> 00:17:26.060
We'll say to that person number one

00:17:26.060 --> 00:17:28.060
That's not the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam in which you saw

00:17:28.060 --> 00:17:30.060
And that is definitely

00:17:30.060 --> 00:17:32.060
Not a ruling that you should take on board

00:17:32.060 --> 00:17:34.060
What you do is what you follow

00:17:34.060 --> 00:17:36.060
Is what is in the Quran and the sunnah

00:17:36.060 --> 00:17:38.060
And this is my sallallahu alayhi wa sallam regarding dreams

00:17:38.060 --> 00:17:40.060
And it's reality inshallah

00:17:40.060 --> 00:17:42.060
I will speak about it somewhere else

00:17:42.060 --> 00:17:44.060
In the name of Allah the most gracious

00:17:44.060 --> 00:17:46.060
So sometimes the dreams can be

00:17:46.060 --> 00:17:48.060
Things that are opposite

00:17:48.060 --> 00:17:50.060
To the shara'i

00:17:50.060 --> 00:17:52.060
Ruling but they have

00:17:52.060 --> 00:17:54.060
Another interpretation

00:17:54.060 --> 00:17:56.060
So the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam here is explaining

00:17:56.060 --> 00:17:58.060
That the dragging of the garment

00:17:58.060 --> 00:18:00.060
Of Umar radiallahu ta'ala

00:18:00.060 --> 00:18:02.060
Is what

00:18:02.060 --> 00:18:04.060
Is the vastness of Umar's religion

00:18:04.060 --> 00:18:06.060
And how strong his deen is

00:18:06.060 --> 00:18:08.060
It has nothing to do with the permissibility

00:18:08.060 --> 00:18:10.060
Of what

00:18:10.060 --> 00:18:12.060
Of a person's garment

00:18:12.060 --> 00:18:14.060
A male's garment can it pull

00:18:14.060 --> 00:18:16.060
On the ground, it can it be below the ankles

00:18:16.060 --> 00:18:18.060
He's not talking about that

00:18:18.060 --> 00:18:20.060
So I hope you will have taken that one board

00:18:20.060 --> 00:18:22.060
And understood that

00:18:22.060 --> 00:18:24.060
Anas radiallahu ta'ala anhu he said

00:18:24.060 --> 00:18:26.060
That the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam he said

00:18:26.060 --> 00:18:28.060
Arham ummati abu bakar

00:18:28.060 --> 00:18:30.060
The most merciful person in my ummah is abu bakar

00:18:30.060 --> 00:18:32.060
Wa ashadduha fideelillahi umar

00:18:32.060 --> 00:18:34.060
And the one that's the strongest

00:18:34.060 --> 00:18:36.060
And toughest on the religion is Umar

00:18:36.060 --> 00:18:38.060
Radiallahu ta'ala anhu

00:18:38.060 --> 00:18:40.060
Also the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:18:40.060 --> 00:18:42.060
Mentioned another dream he had

00:18:42.060 --> 00:18:44.060
Abu hurayr narrated this and he said that the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:18:44.060 --> 00:18:46.060
He said

00:18:46.060 --> 00:18:48.060
The Prophet said I was sleeping

00:18:48.060 --> 00:18:50.060
Ra'aytuni fil jannati

00:18:50.060 --> 00:18:52.060
Fidh amra'atan

00:18:52.060 --> 00:18:54.060
Tatawadda ila jani bi qasrin

00:18:54.060 --> 00:18:56.060
I saw a woman

00:18:56.060 --> 00:18:58.060
So the Prophet said I was sleeping

00:18:58.060 --> 00:19:00.060
And the Prophet was in jannah

00:19:00.060 --> 00:19:02.060
And he saw

00:19:02.060 --> 00:19:04.060
A woman doing wudu

00:19:04.060 --> 00:19:06.060
And she was doing wudu

00:19:06.060 --> 00:19:08.060
Ila jani bi qasrin

00:19:08.060 --> 00:19:10.060
The woman was doing wudu

00:19:10.060 --> 00:19:12.060
On the side of a beautiful palace

00:19:12.060 --> 00:19:14.060
Fa qultu

00:19:14.060 --> 00:19:16.060
I said liman hadha al qasru

00:19:16.060 --> 00:19:18.060
Who is that

00:19:18.060 --> 00:19:20.060
Ya'ni palaces

00:19:20.060 --> 00:19:22.060
Who owns this palace

00:19:22.060 --> 00:19:24.060
Qalu they said

00:19:24.060 --> 00:19:26.060
To me the Prophet said li umara

00:19:26.060 --> 00:19:28.060
That's Umar's palace

00:19:28.060 --> 00:19:30.060
Fa dhkartu ghirata umar

00:19:30.060 --> 00:19:32.060
The Prophet then said I remembered the protective

00:19:32.060 --> 00:19:34.060
Jealousy of Umar

00:19:34.060 --> 00:19:36.060
Fa wallaytu mudibirana

00:19:36.060 --> 00:19:38.060
I looked at the woman I turned my back

00:19:38.060 --> 00:19:40.060
Fa baka umar

00:19:40.060 --> 00:19:42.060
Umar cried and he said

00:19:42.060 --> 00:19:44.060
Bi abi anta ya rasoola Allahi

00:19:44.060 --> 00:19:46.060
A'laika agharu

00:19:46.060 --> 00:19:48.060
Umar cried and he said ya rasoola Allahi

00:19:48.060 --> 00:19:50.060
Am I going to be jealous of you

00:19:50.060 --> 00:19:52.060
Protective jealous of you

00:19:52.060 --> 00:19:54.060
I trust you

00:19:54.060 --> 00:19:56.060
The Prophet of Allah

00:19:56.060 --> 00:19:58.060
Bukhari and Muslim both

00:19:58.060 --> 00:20:00.060
Narrated that

00:20:00.060 --> 00:20:02.060
A'limna bi taribin

00:20:02.060 --> 00:20:04.060
One day he stood on the pulpit of Kufa

00:20:04.060 --> 00:20:06.060
And he did this

00:20:06.060 --> 00:20:08.060
He did this in the presence of many people

00:20:08.060 --> 00:20:10.060
This was Ayyama Khilafati

00:20:10.060 --> 00:20:12.060
The days of his khilafa

00:20:12.060 --> 00:20:14.060
A'limna bi taribin

00:20:14.060 --> 00:20:16.060
He said

00:20:18.060 --> 00:20:20.060
The best man

00:20:20.060 --> 00:20:22.060
After Nabi Allahi Muhammad

00:20:22.060 --> 00:20:24.060
Is Abu Bakr

00:20:26.060 --> 00:20:28.060
And after Abu Bakr

00:20:28.060 --> 00:20:30.060
The best person is Umar

00:20:32.060 --> 00:20:34.060
If you want me to tell you

00:20:34.060 --> 00:20:36.060
The third person

00:20:36.060 --> 00:20:38.060
I can tell you who it is

00:20:38.060 --> 00:20:40.060
This brothers and sisters

00:20:40.060 --> 00:20:42.060
Imam al-Dhahabi

00:20:42.060 --> 00:20:44.060
He said

00:20:44.060 --> 00:20:46.060
This is

00:20:46.060 --> 00:20:48.060
This is

00:20:48.060 --> 00:20:50.060
This is multitude

00:20:50.060 --> 00:20:52.060
Mass transmission

00:20:52.060 --> 00:20:54.060
Of A'limna bi taribin

00:20:54.060 --> 00:20:56.060
Saying this about Abu Bakr and Umar

00:20:56.060 --> 00:20:58.060
And look what he said after that

00:20:58.060 --> 00:21:00.060
Imam al-Dhahabi

00:21:00.060 --> 00:21:02.060
He said

00:21:04.060 --> 00:21:06.060
He said

00:21:06.060 --> 00:21:08.060
He said

00:21:08.060 --> 00:21:10.060
May Allah Ta'ala destroy the Rafid

00:21:10.060 --> 00:21:12.060
Who say otherwise

00:21:12.060 --> 00:21:14.060
Aisha she said

00:21:14.060 --> 00:21:16.060
Abu Bakr said

00:21:16.060 --> 00:21:18.060
Aisha head is from her father Abu Bakr

00:21:18.060 --> 00:21:20.060
Abu Bakr one day he said

00:21:20.060 --> 00:21:22.060
Ma ala dhaher al ardi

00:21:22.060 --> 00:21:24.060
Rajulun ahab

00:21:24.060 --> 00:21:27.950
Ilayya min umara

00:21:27.950 --> 00:21:29.950
Aisha radiya Allah wa ta'ala

00:21:29.950 --> 00:21:31.950
She heard her father

00:21:31.950 --> 00:21:33.950
Abu Bakr saying

00:21:33.950 --> 00:21:35.950
Nobody on the face of this earth today

00:21:35.950 --> 00:21:37.950
More beloved to me than Umar

00:21:37.950 --> 00:21:39.950
Abu Bakr said that

00:21:39.950 --> 00:21:41.950
Aisha also mentioned

00:21:41.950 --> 00:21:43.950
Dakhala naasun ala abi Bakrin

00:21:43.950 --> 00:21:45.950
A group of people they entered onto

00:21:45.950 --> 00:21:47.950
Abi Bakr

00:21:47.950 --> 00:21:49.950
When he was on his death bed

00:21:49.950 --> 00:21:51.950
And they said to him

00:21:51.950 --> 00:21:53.950
Do you think

00:21:53.950 --> 00:21:55.950
It's fit

00:21:55.950 --> 00:21:57.950
That you place

00:21:57.950 --> 00:21:59.950
Over us Umar

00:21:59.950 --> 00:22:01.950
You appoint Umar as the next

00:22:01.950 --> 00:22:03.950
Your next

00:22:03.950 --> 00:22:05.950
Kin in power

00:22:05.950 --> 00:22:07.950
Your next in power

00:22:07.950 --> 00:22:09.950
You place Umar as your successor

00:22:09.950 --> 00:22:11.950
Do you think that's something fit

00:22:11.950 --> 00:22:13.950
That you should do

00:22:13.950 --> 00:22:15.950
Do you think it's a wise decision

00:22:15.950 --> 00:22:17.950
They said that to Abu Bakr

00:22:17.950 --> 00:22:19.950
Do you think it's a wise decision

00:22:19.950 --> 00:22:21.950
To place Umar over us

00:22:21.950 --> 00:22:23.950
And to make him the next leader

00:22:23.950 --> 00:22:25.950
After you go

00:22:25.950 --> 00:22:27.950
To make him your successor

00:22:27.950 --> 00:22:29.950
Do you think it's a wise decision

00:22:29.950 --> 00:22:31.950
And they look what he said

00:22:31.950 --> 00:22:33.950
Abi Bakr

00:22:33.950 --> 00:22:35.950
They said to him

00:22:35.950 --> 00:22:37.950
When you meet Allah what are you going to say

00:22:37.950 --> 00:22:39.950
What's your response

00:22:39.950 --> 00:22:41.950
When Allah asks you why did you place Umar over these people

00:22:41.950 --> 00:22:43.950
What are you going to say

00:22:43.950 --> 00:22:45.950
I will say to

00:22:45.950 --> 00:22:47.950
Allah that I appointed

00:22:47.950 --> 00:22:49.950
The best person I knew for them

00:22:49.950 --> 00:22:51.950
Because Umar

00:22:51.950 --> 00:22:53.950
The reason why they were concerned

00:22:53.950 --> 00:22:55.950
Was because he was strong

00:22:55.950 --> 00:22:57.950
And they were used to

00:22:57.950 --> 00:22:59.950
Umar was soft

00:22:59.950 --> 00:23:01.950
Umar was strong as we mentioned before

00:23:01.950 --> 00:23:03.950
The statement of the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam when he said

00:23:03.950 --> 00:23:05.950
The most merciful person of my Ummah

00:23:05.950 --> 00:23:07.950
Is

00:23:07.950 --> 00:23:09.950
Abi Bakr

00:23:09.950 --> 00:23:11.950
The one who is the strongest

00:23:11.950 --> 00:23:13.950
Upon the religion

00:23:13.950 --> 00:23:15.950
And he's like that is Umar

00:23:15.950 --> 00:23:17.950
And that's why Abd al-Abin al-Saudin

00:23:17.950 --> 00:23:19.950
Mentioned

00:23:19.950 --> 00:23:21.950
If the righteous people are

00:23:21.950 --> 00:23:23.950
Mentioned

00:23:23.950 --> 00:23:25.950
Umar is mentioned there

00:23:25.950 --> 00:23:27.950
He said

00:23:31.950 --> 00:23:33.950
That

00:23:33.950 --> 00:23:35.950
Umar had more

00:23:35.950 --> 00:23:37.950
Knowledgeable in the book of Allah than all of us

00:23:37.950 --> 00:23:39.950
And he had more fiqh in the deen of Allah

00:23:41.950 --> 00:23:43.950
Abd al-Abin al-Saudin saying this by the way right

00:23:43.950 --> 00:23:45.950
Abd al-Abin al-Saud was a alim

00:23:45.950 --> 00:23:47.950
Of the Quran

00:23:47.950 --> 00:23:49.950
Also Abd al-Abin al-Saudin he said

00:23:49.950 --> 00:23:51.950
Arabic

00:23:51.950 --> 00:23:53.950
